(Corrects currency denomination in second paragraph.)  Global Investment House KSCC (GLOBAL)  soared
the most in more than six years after the Kuwaiti bank said its
second-quarter loss narrowed.  The shares surged as much as 11 percent, the most since
February 2005, to 20.5 fils before trading at 20 fils at 10:59
a.m. in Kuwait city.  The company had a loss of 16.7 million dinars ($61 million)
in the second quarter compared with a loss of 20.3 million
dinars in the year earlier period.  To contact the reporter on this story:
